  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "CSS Modules seems to be a new way to style React components (and possibly non React) that is gaining some traction:\n- https://css-tricks.com/css-modules-part-1-need/\n- http://survivejs.com/react/advanced-techniques/styling-react/\n- https://github.com/react-toolbox/react-toolbox (styling is done with CSS modules by default)\n\nNot saying we should always surf the last trend but at least ensure we are compatible with it (reduce the number of times users will hit a wall).\n",
    "created_at": "2016-09-06T08:11:32Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1256#issuecomment-244880047",
